article:
__NOTOC__ '1994' ('[[Roman numerals|MCMXCIV]]') was a common year that started
on a Saturday. In the Gregorian calendar, it was the 1994th year of the Common
Era, or of Anno Domini; the 994th year of the 2nd millennium; the 94th year of
the 20th century; and the 5th of the 1990s. The year 1994 was designated as the
"International Year of the Family" and the "International Year of Sport and the
Olympic Ideal" by the United Nations.
